<HEADLINE>
<P>
BERNARDI RELEASED FROM HOSPITAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
City Councilman Ernani Bernardi left the hospital Monday, five days after he 
hit his head in a fall at his Van Nuys home while suffering from a flu-like 
illness. 
</P>
<P>
The 77-year-old northeast San Fernando Valley councilman required five stitches 
after cutting his head last Wednesday when he stood to answer the phone and, 
weakened by his illness, fainted and fell. 
</P>
<P>
A spokeswoman for Kaiser Permanente Medical Center in Panorama City said 
Bernardi was "stable and doing fine" when he checked out. 
</P>
<P>
The councilman's aides said they did not know when he would return to work. 
</P>
<P>
Bernardi, the council's senior member with nearly 28 years of service, faces an 
election in April. 
</P>
</TEXT>
