<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY SPORTS ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVEN HERBERT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Simi Valley 79, Newbury Park 76 (OT) -- Chris Quirmbach converted a 3-point 
shot for Simi Valley to force overtime and Kenny Hood scored 5 of his game-high 
24 points in overtime as the visiting Pioneers won their 28th consecutive 
Marmonte League game. 
</P>
<P>
Steve Carnes added 21 points and 10 rebounds and Dennis Cook had 12 points for 
Simi Valley (10-5, 3-0). Amir El Farra led Newbury Park (9-4, 0-2) with 18 
points. 
</P>
<P>
Westlake 72, Royal 64 -- Jeff Maurer scored 23 points and Kurt Schwan added 19 
to lead the Warriors (9-6, 2-1) in a Marmonte League game at Royal. 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks 72, Channel Islands 52 -- Mike Sandlin scored 8 of his game-high 
25 points in the third quarter for the Lancers in a Marmonte league game at 
Thousand Oaks. 
</P>
<P>
Oakwood 60, Holy Martyrs 29 -- Mitchell Butler scored 37 points to lead the 
Gorillas (9-2, 3-0) to their fourth consecutive victory in a Liberty League 
game at Oakwood. 
</P>
<P>
GIRLS 
</P>
<P>
Alemany 48, Notre Dame 42 (OT) -- Nicole Miller scored with 14 seconds left to 
force an overtime period and her basket off a rebound gave Alemany the lead for 
good in the extra period. 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks 60, Channel Islands 49 -- Shani Smyth scored a game-high 29 
points and Michelle Palmisano added 19 for Thousand Oaks (14-2, 3-0) in the 
Marmonte League game at Channel Islands. 
</P>
<P>
Louisville 42, Chaminade 31 -- Melanie Sapon scored a game-high 16 points and 
Pam Powers had 6 points and 14 rebounds for the Royals (3-7, 0-2) in a San 
Fernando Valley League game at Chaminade. 
</P>
<P>
Bell-Jeff 45, St. Genevieve 39 -- Andja Vucurevic scored a game-high 25 points 
and had 13 rebounds to lead the Guards (15-3, 2-0) in a San Fernando Valley 
League game at St. Genevieve. 
</P>
<P>
COLLEGE MEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
Valley 68, Glendale 62 -- Joey Manliguis broke open a tie game with 2 free 
throws with 3:13 remaining and added a 3-point basket and 2 more free throws 
during an 8-0 run to lead Valley in a Western State Conference game at 
Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
Andre Bouvay had 17 for Valley (12-8, 2-1). STEVEN HERBERT 
</P>
</TEXT>
