VALLEY ROUNDUP: SUPERIOR INDUSTRIES WINS WHEEL CONTRACT WITH FORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Superior Industries said it has received a five-year contract to supply Ford 
Motor Co. with aluminum wheels for cars and trucks. The contract amount was not 
revealed. 
</P>
<P>
The Van Nuys company said the contract extends from 1989 to 1993. Superior 
makes more than 24 wheel models for Ford, representing annual sales of more 
than $100 million. 
</P>
