<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY ROUNDUP: NOVEMBER HOUSE SALES FALL IN CONEJO VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
November sales of existing houses in the Conejo Valley fell 12% from the 
previous month but remained 24% ahead of a year earlier, the Conejo Valley 
Board of Realtors said. 
</P>
<P>
The board said 230 single-family houses were sold in November, down from 262 in 
October but up from 186 in November, 1987. Sales of condominiums followed a 
similar pattern, totaling 330 in November, which was down from 361 in October 
but up from 245 a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
The average price of a house, meanwhile, fell to $296,906 in November from a 
record high of $303,900 in October, the board said. A year earlier, the average 
price was $236,797. 
</P>
<P>
The report covers sales in Agoura Hills, Westlake Village, Thousand Oaks and 
Newbury Park. 
</P>
</TEXT>
