<TEXT>
<P>
A 10-month-old girl, believed to have spent two cold nights in a drainage ditch 
after her mother was struck by a hit-and-run driver's car while trying to cross 
Interstate 5 on foot with a group of illegal aliens, was in good condition at 
Scripps Memorial Hospital in Chula Vista. The baby, apparently suffering from 
mild hypothermia, was returned to Onecima Lopez, 30, who was in the hospital 
with both legs broken. Lopez told police that another of the group was carrying 
her baby and that she assumed someone would take the child to Los Angeles, 
where her husband had applied to become a legal U.S. resident. The baby, 
however, was found in the drainage ditch by other migrants, who stopped a cab 
driver and told him to take her to police. 
