RAF JET CRASHES IN SEA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DUNDEE, Scotland 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Royal Air Force Phantom jet fighter crashed in the North Sea on Monday during 
a training mission, and the pilot was missing, the air force said. An air force 
helicopter picked up the jet's other crewman, the navigator, from a dinghy near 
the crash site, 52 miles off the eastern Scotland port city of Dundee, an air 
force spokesman said. 
</P>
