<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CAMPBELL'S 53 POINTS CARRY LA QUINTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Scott Campbell scored a school-record 53 points to lead La Quinta High School 
to a 92-63 victory over Bolsa Grande Monday in a Garden Grove League boys' 
basketball game at La Quinta. 
</P>
<P>
Campbell broke John Rogers' school record of 52 set in 1981 and tied the fourth 
highest single-game performance in Orange County history. 
</P>
<P>
Tim Gergen of Rancho Alamitos (1966), Tom Lewis of Mater Dei (1983) and Mike 
Goff of Magnolia (1987) also scored 53 points in a game. Arthur Worthy of 
Huntington Beach holds the county record of 58 points, set in 1910. 
</P>
<P>
"At halftime I thought I had 18 or 20 points, just a regular game for me," said 
Campbell, a 6-foot 5-inch senior forward. "Then someone told me I had 35 and I 
started thinking that Johnny's record was only 52. So I kept shooting and the 
ball kept going in." 
</P>
<P>
Campbell made 17 of 29 shots, including 8 of 9 3-pointers. He left the game 
with more than 5 minutes left. 
</P>
<P>
It was Campbell's seventh consecutive game in which he has scored at least 30 
points. He is averaging 34.6 points per game this season, tops in Orange 
County. 
</P>
<P>
"Things have been going well lately," Campbell said. "I have to give the credit 
to my point guards. They've been getting me the ball in good position to 
score." 
</P>
<P>
Bill Snyder added 13 points and 12 assists for La Quinta. 
</P>
<P>
La Quinta (8-4 overall, 3-0 in league) led, 27-17, at the end of the first 
quarter and 48-31 at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
Bolsa Grande is 1-8 and 0-3. 
</P>
<P>
In other Garden Grove League games. 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy 68, Santiago 36 -- Tom Deep scored 15 points and Mike Pettengill 13 to 
lead Kennedy (9-6, 2-1). Santiago is 0-8 and 0-3. 
</P>
<P>
Pacifica 65 Garden Grove 40 -- Randy Schultze scored 15 points to lead Pacifica 
(8-3, 3-0) at Garden Grove. Garden Grove is 2-10 and 1-2. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Alamitos 81, Los Amigos 59 -- Gary Lira scored 16 points to lead Rancho 
Alamitos (4-5, 2-1) at Los Amigos. Carlos Palomino scored 30 points for Los 
Amigos (2-8, 1-2). 
</P>
<P>
In Garden Grove League girls' basketball: 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy 47, Santiago 44 -- Valeria Ruiz scored 21 points, including a 
game-winning 3-point field goal with 35 seconds left, to lead Kennedy (3-6, 
2-1) at Santiago. Lara Cummins had 13 points and 15 rebounds for Kennedy (3-6, 
2-1). Robin Claires scored 17 points and Beck Elcock added 16 for Santiago. 
</P>
<P>
La Quinta 79, Bolsa Grande 23 -- Amy Jalewalia had 41 points, 13 rebounds and 
10 steals to lead host La Quinta (10-3, 3-0). 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Alamitos 57, Los Amigos 45 -- Jenny Newsome scored 27 points to lead 
Rancho Alamitos (10-1, 2-1) at Los Amigos. Christy Kalbhenn scored 17 points 
for the Vaqueros. Amy Pearson and Angela Fischbeck each scored 12 points for 
Los Amigos (4-7, 2-1). 
</P>
<P>
In Pacific Coast League boys' soccer: 
</P>
<P>
