</P>
<P>
Anaheim 2, Savanna 1 -- A fluke goal gave the Colonists (5-3-1) the victory at 
Savanna. With 2 minutes left and the score tied, 1-1, Savanna 's Marie 
Benavides attempted to get the ball to goalie Carmen Ascencio. However, the 
ball got past Ascencio and went into the net, giving Anaheim a 2-1 lead. April 
Garcia scored midway through the second half to give Anaheim a 1-0 lead. 
Benavides tied the score, 1-1, with 10 minutes left. Ascencio made 18 saves. 
</P>
