<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
L.A. TRAFFIC POLICEMAN ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A veteran Los Angeles police officer assigned to traffic courts has been 
arrested on suspicion of tampering with files in an effort to block prosecution 
of a suspect in a drunk-driving case, investigators reported today. 
</P>
<P>
Police said Officer Edward Romero, 44, a member of the force for 20 years, 
removed a document from a court file in exchange for money. He was released on 
$5,000 bail after his arrest Monday night on an obstruction-of-justice count. 
The suspect in the court case was not immediately identified. 
</P>
</TEXT>
