<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD; 
</P>
<P>
JAPANESE BANKS AID IN RJR BUYOUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ten Japanese banks will lend a total of $5.1 billion to help finance U.S.-based 
Kohlberg Kravis Roberts &amp; Co.'s buyout of RJR Nabisco Inc., a bank official 
said today. 
</P>
<P>
The loan was believed to be the largest ever by Japanese banks for such a 
transaction. The official who provided the figure insisted on not being 
identified by name or bank, although his bank is one of the 10 involved in the 
deal. KKR will be using a total of $14 billion in bank loans to finance its 
record $24.53-billion buyout of RJR Nabisco. Mitsubishi Bank earlier confirmed 
that it had offered KKR a loan, but a bank official declined to specify the 
amount. 
</P>
</TEXT>
