<TEXT>
<P>
A robbery suspect who could not elude a police dog managed to escape from his 
human captors this morning during treatment for dog bite wounds at a Santa Ana 
hospital, Santa Ana police said. 
</P>
<P>
The suspect, Eric Moore, had been captured under a house on West Cubbon Street 
by a police dog Monday after Alfredo Torrez, 36, flagged down officers and said 
two men had taken his wallet and two gold rings, police spokeswoman Maureen 
Thomas said. 
</P>
<P>
